<p>EDIT: I'll keep it for now, only beacuse I'd like to hear what some of the others have to say. Personally, I think we should be moving on to writing "tests" potential applications of 682, such as "Impossible" power sources, or things that turn lead into gold. And what happens when you write gibberish? Or cut and paste lines of dialogue to form somethign incohesive? Or if we sent SCP-056 into <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Sonichu">"Sonichu"</a>… we're barely scratching the surface…</p>

